        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2>ABOUT TeamGenie</h2>
          <p>An introduction to the app the the project</p>
          <hr />
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
          <div class="row">
            <%= image_tag "about-img.png", :alt => "About Us", :class => "img-left" %>
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-lg-offset-3">
              <h3>An App to Make Your Life Easier</h3>
              <p>TeamGenie is a complete sports management platform that takes the pain out of organizing recreational sports teams by providing easy roster management and enabling seamless communication and payment collection. Using TeamGenie, captains can quickly create new teams, add players to their rosters and schedule games. Players are automatically notified and reminded of upcoming games and are invited to RSVP so captains have an accurate head count before game-time. Captains can also email players, text players through the Twilio API and accept payments using a secure Stripe connection.</p>

              <p>The TeamGenie app was created by Ricardo Fleury, Kay Lindenberg and David Vaynshteyn as their final project for Dev Bootcamp. Completed in just eight days, the project is the culmination of an intensive computer development course that turns novice programmers into junior devs. The app features a number of technologies and languages including Ruby, Rails, JavaScript, Postgresql, Sidekiq, Stripe, Redis, Twilio and more. The full GitHub repository is available <a href="https://github.com/chi-fiddler-crabs-2015/TeamGenie">here</a>.</p>
